In a message dated 2/5/2002 7:18:57 AM Pacific Standard Time, 
veadelcro(-at-)juno.com writes:
> My brake pedal started staying down!  The brakes work fine, I just have to 
> pull it back up with the corner of my shoe.  What gives?

Hi Adam, Verna, and Elisabeth,
First check if your brake pedal spring is not broken.  If it is, replace it.
When you replace the spring or not, remove your brake pedal off it's pivot 
for a good cleaning and greasing.  If that does not solve it you need to 
repair or replace the MC.
Eric&Barb




